(8, 1, '<h1 style=\"text-align: justify;\">Instructions for Return</h1><div style=\"text-align: justify;\">Please avoid damage and contamination of the product. If possible, please return the goods to us in original packaging with all accessories and with all packaging components. If necessary, use a protective outer packaging. If you no longer own the original packaging, please provide suitable packaging for adequate protection against transport damage.<br /><br />If possible, please not send the goods back to us as an insured package, and keep the delivery document.<br /><br />Please note that the aforementioned conditions are not a prerequisite for the effective exercise of the right of revocation.</div>', 'Instructions for Returned Goods', '2017-01-19 13:02:21', 1),
(9, 1, '<h1>Battery Law</h1>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">With reference to the sale of batteries or accus or equipment which operate with accus or batteries, we, as a distributor are obliged to inform our customers according to the battery ordinance law of certain regulations and obligations as follows:<br />\\r\\n<br />\\r\\nUsed batteries cannot be thrown into the domestic garbage can. Consumers are by law obligated to bring used batteries to a municipal collecting point or to a local shop.This is free-of-charge.You can also return your used batteries/accus to us. The return shipment has to have sufficient postage and be addressed to:<br />\\r\\n<br />\\r\\n{#SHOP_ADDRESS#}<br />\\r\\n<br />\\r\\nUsed batteries may contain harmful substances or heavy metals, which can be harmful to the environment and health. Furthermore, batteries contain valuable raw materials which can be reused. The environment and {#STORE_NAME#} say thank you.<br />\\r\\n<br />\\r\\n<img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/images/mulltonne.jpg\" style=\"margin-left: 10px; margin-right: 10px; float: left; width: 181px; height: 186px;\" />The garbage can means: batteries and accus may not be thrown into the domestic garbage can.<br />\\r\\nThe symbols under the garbage mean:</p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ul style=\"list-style-position: inside;\">\\r\\n	<li>Pb: battery contains lead</li>\\r\\n	<li>Cd: battery contains cadmium</li>\\r\\n	<li>Hg: battery contains mercury</li>\\r\\n</ul>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p><br />\\r\\n&nbsp;</p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>You have the possibility to read this information again in the papers accompanying the shipment or in the Operating Instructions of the manufacturer.<br />\\r\\n<br />\\r\\nFurther detailed informations regarding the battery ordinance law you receive at the Ministry of Environment, Nature Conservation and Reactor Safety here <a class=\"contentLink\" href=\"http://www.bmu.de/abfallwirtschaft\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.bmu.de/abfallwirtschaft</a> or here <a class=\"contentLink\" href=\"http://www.uba.de\" target=\"_blank\">http://www.uba.de</a>.</p>', 'Battery Law', '2017-01-22 13:14:33', 0),
(11, 1, '<h1>Order Help</h1><strong>Order Sequence</strong><br />Once you have found the desired product, you can place the product noncommittally by clicking the button &quot;ADD TO CART&quot; . By clicking the button &quot;CART CONTENTS&quot; you can noncommittally review all products placed in there. You can easily take a product out of the shopping cart by simply click &quot;REMOVE&quot;. If you want to purchase the products in the shopping cart, you click the button &quot;CHECKOUT&quot;. You are now asked to fill-out your personal information, select the type of payment and confirm acceptance of customer information. At any time you can interrupt the order processing or close the order by clicking the button &quot;CONTINUE&quot;. Naturally you can correct and/or change your given information in the ordering process by pressing the button &quot;RETURN&quot; in your browser. Or you use for your corrections the changing button (EDIT) prior to handing over your order.<br /><br /><strong>Achievement of the Contract</strong><br />The contract language is English. The product representation in our online-shop is not a legal binding offer, but it is a merely noncommittal online-catalog. After input of your personal data and by clicking the button &quot;CONFIRM ORDER&quot; you give a binding order of the products in your shopping cart. Immediately after receipt of your order we send you an acknowledgement indicating that your order has arrived, however, the contract becomes only valid once you have received our order confirmation or delivery of the goods.<br /><br /><strong>Storage of the Contract Text</strong><br />Your order as well as your personal ordering information which you fill-out in our onlineshop prior to your first order, are being stored in your personal customer account. With your login-data which you receive after your first registration, you are now able to log yourself into your personal customer account at anytime. You have the possibility to view your order with all given data and have it printed-out. Furthermore you will receive an order confirmation from us sent to the e-mail address indicated in your order. At anytime you can view and print-out the general contract data under {#SHOP_URL#}', 'Order Help', '2017-01-19 10:20:40', 0),
(12, 1, '<h1>Vouchers - Questions and Answers</h1><div style=\"text-align: justify;\"><strong>Purchasing with a Credit:</strong><br />Vouchers, if offered, can be purchased in the shop just like normal articles.After you have purchased a voucher and payment has been received, you are now able to redeem it under &ldquo;Method of Payment&rdquo;.<br /><br /><strong>Entering a Credit Voucher:</strong><br />If your account shows a credit then you can use it for your new order. You are able to do this during the purchasing process. Should your credit be higher than the value of your order, then you are unable to use the credit. The value of your order has to be at least as high as the credit.Purchasing Credit Vouchers<br /><br /><strong>When you receive a credit voucher via e-mail, you can enter the amount as follows:</strong><br />1. Click at the link in your e-mail. If you don&rsquo;t have your own customer account, then your are now able to open your account.<br />2. During the purchasing process you can manually put-in the Code for &ldquo;Method of Payment&rdquo; Please enter your voucher first and then choose your desired type of payment.<br /><br /><strong>If Problems occur:</strong><br />Should you encounter any problems with a voucher, please contact us via e-mail: {#STORE_OWNER_EMAIL_ADDRESS#}. Please describe your problem in detail. Important informations are: Your customer number, the voucher code, error information of the system as well as the Browser you are using.</div>', 'Gift Voucher FAQ', '2017-01-19 09:59:17', 0),
